        <headline>Flood Warning issued June 18 at 7:51AM CDT until June 23 at 1:00AM CDT by NWS Topeka KS</headline>
        <description>...The National Weather Service in Topeka KS has issued a Flood
Warning for the following rivers in Kansas...

Cottonwood River near Emporia affecting Lyon County.

...Forecast flooding changed from Minor to Moderate severity and
increased in duration for the following rivers in Kansas...

Neosho River Near Neosho Rapids affecting Lyon County.

* WHAT...Moderate flooding is forecast.

* WHERE...Neosho River near Neosho Rapids.

* WHEN...From this evening to early Monday morning.

* IMPACTS...At 22.0 feet, Low lying areas along the river flood.
At 23.0 feet, Water overtops Road 145 on the west side of the
bridge over the Neosho River.
At 26.0 feet, Water covers large areas over both banks.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 7:30 AM CDT Wednesday the stage was 18.3 feet.
- Forecast...The river is expected to rise above flood stage
this evening to a crest of 24.1 feet early Friday morning. It
will then fall below flood stage Sunday morning.
- Flood stage is 22.0 feet.
</description>
        <instruction>

Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive
cars through flooded areas.

This product along with additional weather and stream information is
available at www.weather.gov/top/.</instruction>
